  "title": "Quebec Had a Kangaroo on the Loose. His Name Was Galahad.",
  "script": "Quebec has a kangaroo problem? Galahad — a juvenile kangaroo — escaped from an equestrian stable in Boucherville, on Montreal's South Shore. The SPCA put out the alert on June 13: animal spotted loose in a field, came from a facility that had been keeping it illegally. No permit. No authorization. Just a kangaroo in a horse barn south of Montreal. For days, people spotted Galahad bounding through the area. Tuesday, Quebec's environment ministry teams moved in, sedated him, and he's now headed to the Granby Zoo. The stable faces heat for the illegal captivity. But honestly, the weirdest part is that nobody noticed a kangaroo living there until it left. So: how long WAS Galahad at that Quebec stable before the escape?",
